<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99037729254724></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99037729254724><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99037729254724>RE: Half Elf Bard a Good Idea?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 20th 12:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am also a half elven bard. I like them the best, they start out with the highest Dexterity (only by 5 points, but still, it's the highest) and their Agility's also high.<br>All three start out with the same charisma and intelligence. The half-elf's strength isn't great, but it's not horrible (75) and STA is about the same (70).<br>Going in the order of STR, STA, AGI, DEX, WIS, INT, and CHA, Half elf stats are 75, 70, 90, 95, 60, 75, 85<br>Humans are 80, 75, 75, 85, 75, 75, 85<br>and Wood elves are 70, 65, 95, 90, 80, 75, 85<br>And you still have your 25 honus points to distribute.<br>Hope that helps<br>Plus half-elves are pretty <br>(Though if you're planning on being a female half-elf, I'd try to find some way to cover up that hair)<br><br>(And this is just my opinion, but I like Freeport better than Qeynos as a starting city... though Qeynos is close to Blackburrow. And I miss Blackburrow)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
