<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99031553027687></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99031553027687><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99031553027687>RE: Half Elf Bard a Good Idea?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31993><span id=Scholar>Taamas</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, May 19th 7:38 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.22]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i am a half elf bard and i love him. tho i hear that is bad combo becuz of hybrid race hybrid class and what it does to your xp. i don't really care, i love him anyways  =)  its all up to what you think. i think wood elves have higher defensive stats and cha, while humans are overall average and half elves have more melee based stats. i picked half elf becuz i didn't know much bout a bard, i originally thought he was a war who could sing to buff his grp, thought would be awesome  =)  anyways as i grew up, i noticed the importance of agi and cha and have been spending my time and money seeking those items. so my answer: pick what you want, if you do half elf put 10-15 points into cha then 5-10 into agi and rest into str or dex. for wood elf 10-15 into cha, 0-5 into agi or dex and rest into str. human you should put majority into cha and the rest into agi or dex. if any leftover points, str is a good choice.<br><br>weps don't make the bard, the instrument does.<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>40th Season<br>House of Wargoth<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
