<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99039048358645></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99039048358645><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99039048358645>RE: Half Elf Bard a Good Idea?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 20th 4:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For a bard, don't look too heavily for agility. Dexterity is needed to hit more notes correctly, and charisma is needed for your faction or charming songs.<br><br>For the most part, half elves are the most common of bards because they have the best starting stats for that class. Disregard the hybrid penalties because Verant removed them.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
